<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 3:08PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
northwestern Rockingham, western Pittsylvania, Henry and southeastern
Franklin Counties and the City of Martinsville through 345 PM EDT...
At 307 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Sontag to near Chatmoss to Penns Store.
Movement was east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Martinsville...
Rocky Mount...
Axton...
Penhook...
Spencer...
and Callands.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
